Logical operators operate only on boolean operands and not on numeric operands.
    Operation                   Operator Symbol
    Logical AND                     &
    Logical OR                      |
    Logical XOR                     ^
    Short-circuit OR                ||
    Short-circuit AND               &&
    Logical unary NOT               !
    Equall to                       ==
    Not equall to                   !=
    Ternary if-else                 ?:
    
##Ternary Operator
    expression1 ? expression2 : expression3
        expression1 should alwayas results in boolean value true or false. If the expression1 results in true, expression2 is evaluated and
    expression3 is descarded, otherwise, expression3 is evaluated and expression2 is descarded.
    
    
